### 2026-06-30T16:42:38Z — OtterCopy — Type dropdown now lists all prompts, Extended gated

**Summary.** Follow-up to the declutter work below: the Type dropdown was hardcoded to Task/Handoff, which dropped primary-UI access to the `Summary` and `Variables` prompts (previously reachable via the active-prompt setting on the Basic path). Reworked the dropdown to list the **entire prompt library** (built-ins + user custom) from `promptStore.getPrompts()`, value = prompt id. The **Extended review** toggle is now enabled only for prompts that have an extended pipeline (`prompt-refinement`, `prompt-handoff`) and is disabled + unchecked for all others (single-pass prompts).

**Files/areas.**
- `popup.html` — `#refineType` emptied of hardcoded options (populated dynamically).
- `popup.js` — `EXTENDED_PIPELINE_BY_PROMPT_ID` map; `populateRefineTypes()` (built from `promptConfigs`, preserves selection, called in `initializeSettings` + `renderPromptList`); `updateExtendedGating()` enables/clears the toggle; `runRefine()` sends the selected `promptId` on the Basic path and routes the two chain prompts to their extended actions; prefs now persist `promptId` + `extended`; init reordered to `initializeSettings().then(loadUiPrefs)` so the dropdown exists before prefs restore.
- `background.js` — short path takes `promptId` (replacing the earlier `type` map); selects that prompt, falling back to the active prompt when absent.

**User-visible impact.** All prompts (Refinement, Summary, Variables, Handoff, + any custom) selectable from the primary view. Extended toggle greys out for prompts with no chain, removing a meaningless control state. No reachability regression.

